{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"3385","heading":"Benjamin Tallmadge Institute as primary Central Intelligence Agency entity for education and training in counterintelligence","label":"3385 Benjamin Tallmadge Institute as primary Central Intelligence Agency entity for education and training in counterintelligence","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/ch45/schV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","DefinitionsFor definition of “intelligence community” as used in this section, see , set out as a note under .section 7002 of Pub. L. 118–31section 3003 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Director of the Central Intelligence Agency shall maintain the Benjamin Tallmadge Institute as the primary entity within the Central Intelligence Agency for education and training related to all aspects of counterintelligence.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Responsibilities of Director","label":"b Responsibilities of Director","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"ensure the Institute is fully and properly organized and has the resources necessary to provide counterintelligence education and training for all career fields within the Agency, including specialized certifications for Agency counterintelligence personnel;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"counterintelligence threats, insider threats, and other counterintelligence processes and issues;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the conduct and support of counterintelligence inquiries and investigations;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fb%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"relevant skills necessary for coordination with Federal law enforcement; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fb%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any other skills as the Director determines necessary;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"identify and designate specific positions for which an individual shall be required to have a certification described in paragraph (2) prior to filling such a position; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"develop necessary infrastructure and capacity to support the availability of courses under subsection (c) to increase participation by personnel from other components of the intelligence community in the courses offered by the Institute.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Training and familiarization courses","label":"c Training and familiarization courses","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"develop training and familiarization courses at different classification levels, including courses at an unclassified level; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"offer instruction in the courses developed under subparagraph (A) or make training curricula available to other intelligence community components, as appropriate, to support outreach efforts.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Availability of courses","label":"2 Availability of courses","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Federal departments and agencies that are not elements of the intelligence community.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"State, local, and Tribal governments.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fc%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Private sector entities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fc%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Such other personnel and entities as appropriate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Baseline certification course","label":"d Baseline certification course","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Institute shall develop, in coordination with the National Counterintelligence and Security Center and the Defense Intelligence Agency, and implement a baseline certification course for all counterintelligence career professionals that aligns the minimum certification requirements of the course and the Defense Counterintelligence Agent Course of the Joint Counterintelligence Training Activity.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Availability of course","label":"2 Availability of course","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3385/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3385%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The baseline certification course developed under paragraph (1) shall be made available, on a space-available basis, to all intelligence community professionals and appropriate personnel with appropriate security clearance from any other agency, committee, commission, office, or other establishment in the executive, legislative, or judicial branch of the Federal Government.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
